						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Ghana-Liberia-fisheries-commissions-to-deploy-geo-information-systems-GIS" title="Ghana, Liberia fisheries commissions to deploy geo-information systems (GIS) " alt="link">Ghana, Liberia fisheries commissions to deploy geo-information systems (GIS) </a></h2>

	
					<p>GIS solutions developed by the SuperGeo, a Taiwan-based enterprise, have been chosen by Ghana and Liberia’s fisheries commissions. The technology will enable the personnel at the Fisheries Commissions to develop a GIS system for fishery resource analyses and management. The GIS will be used to visualize and analyze the geographical distributions of marine living resources in that area. Will the system be able to track fishing vessel and monitor catch quality and yield? The <a href="http://www.cersgis.org/" target="_self">Centre for Remote Sensing and Geographic Information Services</a> at the University of Ghana provided guidance on the choice of software.(SuperGeo, 30/7/2012)</p>
							<p><span class="date">14/09/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Ghana-Liberia-fisheries-commissions-to-deploy-geo-information-systems-GIS">Read more...</a>
