						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Tanzanian-Minister-of-Agriculture-and-AGRA-President-challenge-African-leadership-to-take-food-security-action" title="Tanzanian Minister of Agriculture and AGRA President challenge African leadership to take food security action" alt="link">Tanzanian Minister of Agriculture and AGRA President challenge African leadership to take food security action</a></h2>

	
					<p>The forum brings together African Heads of State, ministers, private agribusiness firms, financial institutions, farmers, NGOs, civil society organizations and scientists to discuss and develop concrete investment plans for scaling agricultural development success in Africa. The forum which takes place from September 26 to 28, 2012 will focus on unlocking Africa’s agricultural potential by empowering smallholder farmers across the continent. By collaborating with farmer’s organizations, civil society and other partners, the discussions will explore new ways to provide resources, overcome challenges and improve yields for the millions of farmers who are working less than two hectares of land across the continent.(AfricaBrains, 23/8/2012)</p>
							<p><span class="date">14/09/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Tanzanian-Minister-of-Agriculture-and-AGRA-President-challenge-African-leadership-to-take-food-security-action">Read more...</a>
